    <item>
      <title>Modding games</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/personal/modding_games/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 16:03:09 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/personal/modding_games/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;learning-experience&#34; class=&#34;mt-6 mb-2 text-lg sm:text-xl text-white&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;relative inline-block&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;      Learning experience&#xD;&#xA;      &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute left-0 -bottom-1 h-px w-0 bg-indigo-400&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Some time ago I got interested in modding with &lt;strong&gt;Arma reforger&lt;/strong&gt; game.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I wanted to contribute to my servers gaming community with custom content to suit our needs and just to make cool stuff.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;At first I started off with some simple assets and objects that can be placed in the world by a Game Master.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
